          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2016-07-07T17:45:32Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong></strong><b>Student Loan Bankruptcy Parity Act of 2015</b></p> <p>This bill amends the federal bankruptcy code to eliminate the provision that makes certain education debts non-dischargeable in bankruptcy unless repayment imposes an undue hardship. </p> <p>Specifically it permits a borrower to discharge in bankruptcy a nonprofit, government, or private student loan, or an obligation to repay an educational benefit, scholarship, or stipend. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2015-09-08T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
